				id: "463279A76283B953"
				item: "mysticalagriculture:prudentium_essence"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Prudentium Essence"
			x: 4.0d
			y: -5.0d
		}
		{
			description: ["Botany Pots grow any plantable item in a compact single-block footprint — Pam's HarvestCraft seeds, vanilla crops, saplings, vines, mushrooms, and most modded plants. They require no sunlight, no farmland, and no irrigation. Soul Land spirit herbs can be grown in Botany Pots using the appropriate soil type, making them the passive indoor source for cultivation-speed alchemicals. A shelf of Botany Pots in your base runs continuously regardless of chunk loading state, producing steady output with zero player attention."]
			id: "7F19B559E12AA6C0"
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
				id: "2725CD07A7CE6FC4"
				item: "kubejs:coin"
				type: "item"
			}]
			tasks: [{
				id: "28F05F0FF04068D3"
				item: "botanypots:botany_pot"
				type: "item"
			}]
			title: "Botany Pot"
			x: -1.0d
			y: -7.5d
		}
		{
			description: ["The Hopper Botany Pot adds an auto-output slot that connects to hoppers and item pipes below the block. Link it to a sorted chest network via Create conveyors or GT item pipes and the pot outputs its harvest automatically on maturity — no player interaction required. A wall of Hopper Botany Pots growing Soul Land spirit herbs, each sorted by herb type into labeled chests, provides the passive cultivation alchemy supply that supports higher cultivation ranks without regular Spirit Beast Forest expeditions."]
			id: "4A826D4AF741D1C0"
			optional: true
			rewards: [{
				count: 3
